Q1  ***Processing a customer order at a restaurant***
Start
Read Order, Quantity
Display "Your Order is, " Order
Display "Your Quantity is, " Quantity
Display "You want an addon? (Y/N)"
Read Continue
If Continue == 'Y' THEN
  Read Special_Request
  Display "Your Add on is, " Special_Request
  Display "Preparing Order"
Else
  Display "Preparing Order"
End


Q2 ***Handling a customer's deposit transaction at a Bank***
Start
Input Acc_No, Deposit
If Acc_No == 'T' THEN
  If Deposit > 0 THEN
    Acc_Balance = Deposit + Acc_Balance
    Print "Deposited Amount is " Deposit
  Else 
    Print "Invalid Amount"
Else 
  Print "Account not found"
End

Q3 ***Find the Greatest Number out of 3***
Start
Input Num1, Num2, Num3
If Num1 > Num2 AND Num1 > Num3 THEN
  Print "Greatest number is, " Num1
Else If Num2 > Num1 AND Num2 > Num3 THEN
  Print "Greatest number is, " Num2
Else 
  Print "Greatest number is, " Num3
End


Q4 ***Displaying Months***
1. Ask the user to enter a NUMBER between 1 and 12.
2. Store the NUMBER in a variable x.
3. Check if 0 < x < 12 to verify that number is in the range or not.
  ~If not in range, display an error message telling invalid input.
4. Use If-else conditions to match the input NUMBER with the corresponding month.
5. Display the month.


Q5 ***Small Calculator***
Start
Declare Addition = 0
Declare Subtraction = 0
Input Num1, Num2, Operator
If Operator == '+' THEN
  Addition = Num1 + Num2
  Print "Your Answer is " Addition
Else
  Subtraction = Num1 - Num2
  Print "Your Answer is " Subtraction
End

